	  WHAT IS THIS        some words about amserv and fileservers.
	@{" CONTENTS           " Link "content"} what this archive should contain.
	@{" USAGE              " Link "usage"} launching and parameters.
	@{" INSTALLING         " Link "install"} installing, simple!
	@{" SETTING UP AMIRC   " Link "setting"} configurating.
	@{" RUNNING IT         " Link "running"} launching it for the first time.
	@{" SHORT FAQ          " Link "faq"} a short frequently asked questions.
	@{" MORE HELP?         " Link "morehelp"} the author.
	@{" HISTORY            " Link "history"} some words from the past.


What is this
============
AmServ is a FileServer (FServe) to be executed under AmIRC 2.x or
higher by Oliver Wagner. You can let users dir your given filearea.
They can UPLOAD and DOWNLOAD to and from it. You set how much credits
a newuser should have, what file ratio, directory-description etc..

Purpose:
AmServ was created for trading and serving files with users.

AmServ is based on the irc-fileservers on PC (FSERVE like PaNzEr)
(but hey if you dont know  what that is, take a look in mp3 or pics
channels #MP3 or #teensexpics etc ;) i promis you will understand what it
is all about.) I also added a link to my page about FServe's
http://home.powertech.no/hanspd/amserv.html click on "How to use a FServe"
@endnode


